text: Nizhnemancharovo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Semiletovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 549 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 19 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Nizhnemancharovo
